	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				It sounds like you are confusing this with the Mage spell &quot;Summon Bandages.&quot;  Bind Affinity has nothing to do with bandages, summoned or otherwise, and it has nothing to do with the Bind Wounds skill.  It resets the place where you will reappear after you die or cast the Gate spell.<BR>
<BR>
Go up to a newbie zone guard and attack it.  That place you just appeared at is called your &quot;bind point.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
Those who can cast it themselves may bind themselves to any location.  To cast it for others you have to group with them and be in a zone which is considered a &quot;city&quot; zone or a location which has been made bindable (such as the gypsy camp in NK).
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
